---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words With Double O — VOODOO, BAMBOO, TABOO, TATTOO" description="Top double-O Scrabble words: VOODOO (10pts), BAMBOO (12pts), TABOO (7pts), TATTOO (6pts). Master OO pattern strategy for vowel-heavy racks." keywords="scrabble double o words, voodoo scrabble, bamboo scrabble, taboo scrabble, tattoo scrabble, double o strategy, oo words scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words With Double O — VOODOO, BAMBOO, TABOO, TATTOO","description":"Master double-O words in Scrabble: VOODOO (10pts), BAMBOO (12pts), TABOO (7pts), TATTOO (6pts) with OO pattern strategy.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-o"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best double-O words in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"BAMBOO (12pts) leads with B(3)+A(1)+M(3)+B(3)+O(1)+O(1). VOODOO (10pts) uses V worth 4 points. TABOO (7pts) and TATTOO (6pts) are shorter options. VOODOO is notable for having three O tiles — useful when your rack is vowel-heavy."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many O tiles are in a Scrabble bag?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"There are 8 O tiles in a standard Scrabble bag, each worth 1 point. O is the 3rd most common vowel after E (12) and A (9). Drawing two or more O's is common, making OO words essential knowledge."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are double-O words good for vowel-heavy racks?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — double-O words like VOODOO (3 O's), BAMBOO, TABOO, and TATTOO help dump excess vowels while scoring. With 8 O tiles in the bag, vowel-heavy racks happen often. These words convert a problem rack into points."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With Double O — OO Pattern Strategy</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">With 8 O tiles in the bag, drawing multiple O's is inevitable. Double-O words turn that surplus into points. BAMBOO leads at 12 points with two 3-point B tiles, VOODOO scores 10 using all three O's from a vowel-heavy rack, and TABOO and TATTOO offer quick 5-letter plays. The OO pattern is your best friend when the bag hands you vowels.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">O Tiles in Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1pt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Per O Tile</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (BAMBOO)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">O's in VOODOO</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Double-O Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 BAMBOO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 points · 6 letters · B(3)+A(1)+M(3)+B(3)+O(1)+O(1) · Double B power</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 VOODOO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 points · 6 letters · V(4)+O(1)+O(1)+D(2)+O(1)+O(1) · Uses 3-4 O tiles</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ TABOO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 points · 5 letters · T(1)+A(1)+B(3)+O(1)+O(1) · Short and reliable</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ TATTOO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">6 points · 6 letters · T(1)+A(1)+T(1)+T(1)+O(1)+O(1) · Uses 3 T's + 2 O's</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">OO Pattern Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Vowel dump plays:</span> VOODOO uses 3-4 O tiles in one play — perfect when your rack is O-heavy. BAMBOO and TABOO each use 2. These convert excess vowels into 7-12 points instead of an exchange.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Pair OO with premium consonants:</span> BAMBOO works because B is worth 3 points (appears twice = 6). When you have OO + high-value consonants (B, M, V), look for these patterns first.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Shorter OO options:</span> BOOK (10), BOOT (6), FOOD (8), GOOD (6), MOON (6), POOL (6), ROOF (7), WOOD (8). These 4-letter OO words work in tight spots and on premium squares.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BAMBOO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VOODOO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TABOO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TATTOO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">O is the <span class="text-white font-medium">3rd most common vowel</span> (8 tiles). Drawing 2-3 O's happens regularly. Instead of exchanging, play BAMBOO (12pts) or VOODOO (10pts) — you'll score points while clearing the vowel glut from your rack.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-double-o/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing Double O</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/vowel-heavy-rack-solutions/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Vowel-Heavy Rack Solutions</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-e/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With Double E</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all double-O words from your tiles — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
